origin.tag_list: Gotharman "little deformer"
origin.title: DEMO Gotharman Little DeFormer oscillators DEMO
origin.description:
Demo of the new Oscilator section the deFormer update. Flemming doesn't do things by half, this update is pretty amazing. Also demo'd are the new LFO and Random functions and the reset sequence (per track).

The oscillators sound very good and make the LD a pretty powerful and amazing box. The sequencer tracks can now all run different amounts of steps there are a load of LFO's that have non linear shapes for doing FM. There are also some random modulators that are triggered by the sequencer. agh, theres loads more too, check it out, grab one, its the best and coolest box out there at the moment for making sounds with. It feels like an old 80's sampler/module or something but just does such brilliant things. Flemming for president!

origin.tag_list: "MOS Recordings" "MOS Deep" Delsin "Ike Release" "Innerspace Halflife" "Dream Sequencer EP" "Cosmic Supreme" Spells Westview
origin.title: Ike Release - Cosmic Supreme [Mos Deep 015]
origin.description:
Following on from his increasingly essential work as Innerspace Halflife, Ike Release steps out on his own for a new three tracker on MOS Deep that finds the Chicago producer in a bullish mood.

Opener 'Cosmic Supreme' is a moody march across the surface of a planet far from here – typically raw, bobbling drums set the tone as a frazzled and drawn out synth line winds right through its core from start to finish. 'Spells' is backlit with an ethereal synthy glow as another thick analogue line takes the main focus of the track, all the while as nebulous percussion floats about like a cloud of dust in the background.

Finally, 'Westview' is a little more propulsive, driven as it is by a lashing, rubberised bassline that sprays about freely, contained only by the itchy and more regimented hi-hats that slice up and down around it. Despite there being a sonic denseness to all three tracks here, a certain emotional gravitas always lurks with in: be it one of introspection or reflection, they are difficult to ignore.
